message.content: Most men in Sweden have a positive and accepting attitude towards divorce. They view it as a normal part of life and believe that individuals have the right to end a marriage if they are unhappy or incompatible with their partner. Men in Sweden generally support gender equality and believe that both men and women should have the freedom to make decisions about their relationships. They also prioritize the well-being of children involved in divorce and strive for fair and equal custody arrangements. Overall, Swedish men tend to have a progressive and open-minded perspective on divorce.
